GalileanTimeTransformation

The Galilean Transformation for Time

Time is the same in all inertial reference frames.

t = t^{\prime}

where:

t [var. scal. Time, T, s] is the time of an event in frame $S$
t^{\prime} [var. scal. Time, T, s] is the time of an event in frame $S^{\prime}$

